//Daemon threads
-- Daemon thread means : a thread which is running in background, Daemon thread will ignored by the JVM
JVM didn't care about the daemon thread



-- synchronization
-- when multiple thread try to access same resources any generate the inconsistent output
which is called race condition and synchronized keyword prevent this race condition.

--mutual exclusion
means that multiple thread can't able access the critical resources at one time.
